text:
So basically, what you have to do in the last part is, well, Fnaf gameplay (survive in an isolated room)

You have a total of 5 batteries

You'll have to use 4 batteries to slowly charge up the machine behind the computer

CatNap will approach you, use the terminate (the smoke thrower) to stop him

If he approaches from the left side, you'll have to use the purple hand, jump up onto the boxes to charge the terminate

If he approaches from the right, open the big door and you'll see the terminate 

If he approaches from above, close the vent door

When the machine is fully charged, use your green hand and it'll show you a cutscene which means the end of the bossfight

While the first two chapters are fun puzzle and chase scenarios this thirst entry is a straight up horror game heavily inspired by the Silent Hill Games more than anything. text:
Although this chapter is conceptually very interesting, and with an incredible new ambience to boot...

Man, the script for this chapter was written completely in yappanese. SO MANY pointless puzzles broken down into even more pointless puzzles for a scrap of story.

There was so much filler puzzle solving that I thought it was a Genshin Character story quest lol.

And, despite the incredible design and ambience, the Catnap chase was far less climatic compared to the first two.

Both of the first boss chases, a.k.a Huggy and Mommy, had a few things in common. You get a cinematic build up (with Huggy slowly walking towards you, and Mommy giving you a headstart) and then the chase picks up, and you need to get the hell away through narrow escape ways with a monster right behind.

Meanwhile, with Catnap, you need to avoid this permanently slow-walking cat in a open area while solving yet another battery puzzle.

Idk if the chase picks up AFTER the battery puzzle, hopefully it does.
